---
/**
 * HVCO opt-in page (/hvco/) — STANDALONE funnel entry point.
 * No site header/footer, no cross-links to the homepage (original scope).
 *
 * Copy SSOT: Deliverables/.../06-canonical-copy/hvco-copy.md — verbatim,
 * zero fixes ("chocked full" carried as-is; doubled periods are brand voice).
 * The corpus "Notes for Claude" section never renders here.
 *
 * KNOWN GAPS (hvco-copy.md Flags — Ben decisions, NOT builder inventions):
 *   - No CTA button text            → [PENDING BEN: cta-label]
 *   - No email-field label          → [PENDING BEN: email-field-label]
 *   - No privacy line               → [PENDING BEN: privacy-line]
 *   - No post-submit confirmation   → [PENDING BEN: confirmation-copy]
 *   - No display headline exists    → page opens straight into the hook copy (by design)
 *   - Asset title unratified (three names in circulation) — "Audio Visual
 *     Mastery for Event Planners" rendered because it IS in the canonical copy.
 *   - No imagery slots defined for this page anywhere in the corpus — none invented.
 * The homepage footer's privacy line is NOT borrowed (explicitly disallowed).
 */
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const juggling = [
  "Securing the venue..",
  "Selecting a caterer and menu",
  "Invites and RSVPs",
  "Booking the talent..",
] as const;

const offerBullets = [
  "How to optimize for maximum connection and impact",
  "How to get the AV piece sorted in minutes, not months",
  "How to properly vet AV companies to lock in on the right partner",
  "How to apply the 80/20 principle to AV budgeting",
  "How to pull off killer production value for less than the cost of the mediocre option",
] as const;
---

<!-- [PENDING BEN: ratify asset title for <title> + og tags] — "Free Guide" is a
     provisional tab/SEO label only (WCAG 2.4.2 distinct-title fix, Vera MEDIUM-3);
     no visible body copy is affected. -->
<BaseLayout title="AV Ninjas | Free Guide">
  <main id="main" class="hvco">
    <!-- 1. Headline / Hook -->
    <section class="section section--roomy" aria-label="Hook">
      <div class="container hvco-narrow">
        <p class="lead">Planning a meeting or event can be a bit like a juggling act:</p>
        <ul>
          {juggling.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
        </ul>
        <p>The list goes on...</p>
        <p>To succeed, it seems like you need to be part plate spinner and part cat-herder..</p>
        <p>
          But it can be absolute magic when all those pieces come together. There's
          nothing quite like the chemistry that can happen at a live event. It's why we do
          what we do. Whether a strategic summit or a conference, something happens when
          you get people in a room together, fully engaged, fully present.
        </p>
        <p>
          ..and for those of us who are drawn to this line of work, it's a point of pride
          to orchestrate all of these pieces, all the while making it look easy.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 2. The Problem (Agitation) -->
    <section class="section section--cream" aria-label="The Problem">
      <div class="container hvco-narrow">
        <p>
          But there's one puzzle piece that can be a bit like Pandora's box. It looks
          innocent enough at first, but it's chocked full of stinging things that can not
          only mess up your day, but do lasting harm to your reputation. If you've ever
          experienced this, you know what I'm talking about.
        </p>
        <p>
          Solid Audio-Visual support can help your event go as smooth as butter, but the
          wrong players can make your event look like hot-mess amateur-hour at best or
          turn it into a full blown train wreck at worst.
        </p>
        <p>
          ..not to mention the unplanned costs that can pile up, seemingly out of nowhere
          - and burn well beyond your budget like a forest fire..
        </p>
        <p>
          ..and the emails. So many emails. Details that never seem to get all the way
          ironed out.. Until you wake up one day and realize that all of the
          back-and-forth has become a second full time job.
        </p>
        <p>
          Being out of sync with your AV provider is a bit like being forced to chew on
          shards of broken glass. It can be incredibly awkward and leave you questioning
          your own sanity. And sadly, piss-poor service and even forms of gaslighting have
          become all too normal in certain settings.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 3. The Turn -->
    <section class="section" aria-label="The Turn">
      <div class="container hvco-narrow">
        <p class="lead">
          It doesn't have to be this way.. In fact, it can be an enjoyable experience.
          Whether you're planning an event for 25 or 2500, you'll find our free resource
          to be worth its weight in gold.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. Offer + opt-in -->
    <section class="section section--roomy section--dark" aria-label="Offer">
      <div class="container hvco-narrow">
        <!-- Asset title pending Ben's ratification (three names in circulation) —
             rendered because this string IS canonical copy. -->
        <h1>Audio Visual Mastery for Event Planners</h1>
        <p class="lead"><em>Everything you need to know. Nothing you don't.</em></p>
        <ul class="hvco-offer-list">
          {offerBullets.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
        </ul>

        <!-- Opt-in mechanics: NO canonical strings exist (hvco-copy.md Flag #1).
             Visibly-marked placeholders below; form is NOT wired (Mack's layer). -->
        <form class="hvco-form" method="post" action="#">
          <div class="field">
            <label for="hvco-email">[PENDING BEN: email-field-label]</label>
            <input type="email" id="hvco-email" name="email" autocomplete="email" required />
          </div>
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary">[PENDING BEN: cta-label]</button>
          <p class="small hvco-privacy">[PENDING BEN: privacy-line]</p>
        </form>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hvco-narrow {
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .hvco-offer-list li {
    padding-block: var(--space-xs);
  }
  .hvco-form {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    max-width: 480px;
  }
  .hvco-form .field {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  .hvco-form :global(input) {
    border-color: var(--color-gray-bright);
  }
  .hvco-privacy {
    color: var(--color-gray-bright);
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>
